Description: 
    YouTube RSS feed aggregator using fzf.

Usage: xl-yt <Option>

Option: One of the following:

    -h , --help:
        Print this help page.

    -a, --add: <URL> , clip
        Add supplied link to list of feeds. You can use clip 
        keyword instead of URL to use link from clipboard instead.
        (both wl-clipboard and xclip are supported)

    -c, --change:
        Edit subscriptions with your EDITOR.

    -u, --update:
        Update subscription feed.

    -v, --view:
        View subscription feed.

    -i, --import: <FILE>
        Import subscriptions (NewPipe JSON) from previous export.

    -e, --export: <FILENAME> (name without .json extension)
        Export subscriptions (NewPipe JSON) to current directory.

Subscriptions:
    They are added into ~/.config/xlotus/ytsubs

    Do not add subscriptions manually to this file and use
    --add instead

    Syntax: <CHANNEL NAME>;;;<RSS FEED URL>
